WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:07.000
Hello, dear colleagues!

00:07.000 --> 00:14.000
My practical experience allows me to share with you some of the techniques that have been developed over this time.

00:14.000 --> 00:23.000
Today we will discuss the topic of the promotion of goods, the promotion of new goods to the market or existing goods.

00:23.000 --> 00:29.000
The demand for advertising from the owners of companies is growing every year.

00:29.000 --> 00:37.000
Promotion of goods to the market, support of loyalty of customers and, as a result, increase of profitability of the company

00:37.000 --> 00:42.000
become the main goal and the main guarantee of the success of the company on the market.

00:42.000 --> 00:49.000
Only a competent setting of goals, as well as clear planning, allows to achieve successful results.

00:49.000 --> 00:59.000
Today we will discuss the various promotion tools that will allow you to achieve success and stand on the high competitive market.

00:59.000 --> 01:05.000
There are several main tools that we will discuss.

01:05.000 --> 01:07.000
The first is advertising.

01:07.000 --> 01:15.000
We will look at the existing advertising tools, which of them are more effective, less effective

01:15.000 --> 01:19.000
and what are the trends of development in the advertising market today.

01:19.000 --> 01:24.000
The next tool that we will consider is, of course, PR.

01:24.000 --> 01:30.000
PR helps companies to better present themselves on the market, position themselves,

01:30.000 --> 01:36.000
and also look more positive in the eyes of the public,

01:36.000 --> 01:43.000
thus maintaining loyal customers and optimizing costs for advertising and marketing.

01:43.000 --> 01:46.000
The next tool is sales promotion.

01:46.000 --> 01:55.000
Sales promotion is the most effective tool for short-term goals, for increasing the company's turnover.

01:55.000 --> 02:01.000
We will also consider several practical methods that will allow you to achieve such results.

02:01.000 --> 02:06.000
The next tools are direct marketing and personal sales,

02:06.000 --> 02:14.000
which are also quite effective if you act according to the given algorithm.

02:14.000 --> 02:21.000
In conclusion, we will look at how to calculate the effectiveness of certain events.

02:21.000 --> 02:28.000
This is perhaps the key point and key issue for marketers and advertisers in companies.

02:28.000 --> 02:34.000
Marketing communication is divided into at least two parts today.

02:34.000 --> 02:37.000
You can see it on the slide.

02:37.000 --> 02:50.000
This is ATL or above the line, and below the line.

02:50.000 --> 02:56.000
There is a legend that one of the managers of one of the large companies,

02:56.000 --> 03:01.000
they say it was in Procter & Gamble, decided to calculate the costs for marketing.

03:01.000 --> 03:06.000
He calculated the costs for exhibitions, advertising, media,

03:06.000 --> 03:12.000
additional events that need to be held to support sales.

03:12.000 --> 03:17.000
He drew a line, but remembered that he forgot a few more things.

03:17.000 --> 03:21.000
This is the promotion of sales, this is the holiday of the city.

03:21.000 --> 03:28.000
Thus, having calculated the final cost, he received all the costs for marketing.

03:28.000 --> 03:33.000
Since then, all costs for marketing are divided into two parts.

03:33.000 --> 03:36.000
You can see this division on the slide.

03:36.000 --> 03:45.000
Although today this line is erased, and today there is no clear division.

03:45.000 --> 03:51.000
Nevertheless, in the field of marketing, in the theory of marketing, it got its continuation.

03:52.000 --> 03:55.000
Everything above the line is considered a general advertising,

03:55.000 --> 03:59.000
and it includes advertising in the media, advertising on television,

03:59.000 --> 04:04.000
advertising on the Internet, and transport advertising.

04:04.000 --> 04:08.000
Everything below the line is related to the promotion of sales,

04:08.000 --> 04:13.000
promotion in trade channels, promotion of the end consumer,

04:13.000 --> 04:18.000
exhibitions, sponsorship, all this is related to BTL.

04:18.000 --> 04:24.000
Thus, in this division, we will consider these tools.

04:24.000 --> 04:31.000
First of all, let's talk about market trends, advertising costs.

04:31.000 --> 04:37.000
On the slides, you can see what trend of advertising costs exists today,

04:37.000 --> 04:42.000
and even the forecast of market experts, what will happen in the future.

04:42.000 --> 04:46.000
We see that a large part is taken by advertising on television.

04:46.000 --> 04:50.000
Despite the fact that it becomes less and less effective,

04:50.000 --> 04:53.000
since the information flows are very large,

04:53.000 --> 04:55.000
and many people simply do not perceive this advertising,

04:55.000 --> 04:58.000
often switch channels, which we often do.

04:58.000 --> 05:03.000
Nevertheless, advertising on television, its costs, its turnover will grow.

05:03.000 --> 05:07.000
And they will grow due to the fact that new goods will be promoted,

05:07.000 --> 05:09.000
the market will be more competitive,

05:09.000 --> 05:12.000
and more and more television channels will appear.

05:13.000 --> 05:16.000
Naturally, due to this, the turnover of advertising will grow.

05:16.000 --> 05:20.000
Advertising is approximately stagnant in mass media,

05:20.000 --> 05:23.000
in other, printed, industry publications.

05:23.000 --> 05:28.000
Nevertheless, the turnover with the growth of the market will increase in the same way,

05:28.000 --> 05:32.000
the share will remain approximately the same.

05:32.000 --> 05:38.000
And if we look at the costs of external advertising,

05:38.000 --> 05:41.000
we see that the share of external advertising is decreasing,

05:41.000 --> 05:44.000
and will decrease, because the streets of our cities

05:44.000 --> 05:47.000
are already practically overflowing with external advertising.

05:47.000 --> 05:50.000
There is a tendency to reduce such advertising.

05:50.000 --> 05:54.000
Let's also pay attention to the trend of the development of the BTL market.

05:54.000 --> 05:58.000
The BTL market is growing, and in three years,

05:58.000 --> 06:02.000
looking at the table, you will see that in three years it has grown by two times.

06:02.000 --> 06:04.000
This is a very serious trend.

06:05.000 --> 06:07.000
It comes to us from the Western market.

06:07.000 --> 06:12.000
In the West, about half of the costs are general advertising,

06:12.000 --> 06:16.000
and about half are costs for BTL.

06:16.000 --> 06:19.000
In our Russian market, the trend is different.

06:19.000 --> 06:26.000
To date, only 5-10, a maximum of 15% of the most advanced companies

06:26.000 --> 06:28.000
spend on BTL.

06:28.000 --> 06:31.000
Nevertheless, as you can see, they are growing dynamically.

06:32.000 --> 06:34.000
Why is this happening?

06:34.000 --> 06:40.000
This happens for several reasons, and we will discuss them now.

06:40.000 --> 06:44.000
The first reason is a large number of branded goods with the same properties.

06:44.000 --> 06:50.000
We come to the store and see a lot of products under different brands,

06:50.000 --> 06:53.000
but they are practically impossible to distinguish by properties.

06:53.000 --> 06:58.000
They differ in price, they differ in name, but have the same characteristics.

06:58.000 --> 07:02.000
As a result, we have a hard time choosing what to buy.

07:02.000 --> 07:09.000
BTL helps us choose a product, because there are auctions,

07:09.000 --> 07:14.000
because we are reminded of a particular product, and we pay attention to it again.

07:14.000 --> 07:19.000
BTL gives immediate results in sales.

07:19.000 --> 07:23.000
The next reason is the lack of an original image idea for advertising.

07:23.000 --> 07:28.000
Yes, creativity is great, and it is wonderful to come up with a new idea.

07:28.000 --> 07:32.000
Many companies are now making a breakthrough in this market,

07:32.000 --> 07:34.000
but as we can see, competition is getting tougher.

07:34.000 --> 07:38.000
It is very easy to repeat this idea, and competitors do it.

07:38.000 --> 07:42.000
By repeating the idea, creativity and exclusivity are lost.

07:42.000 --> 07:46.000
And we merge again in a single stream with all the other products.

07:46.000 --> 07:51.000
Therefore, to maintain creativity, you need a lot of costs.

07:51.000 --> 07:54.000
Various agencies, different views on a particular product.

07:54.000 --> 07:58.000
That is why we are again inclined to BTL advertising,

07:58.000 --> 08:01.000
which allows you to achieve immediate results.

08:01.000 --> 08:04.000
The next reason is the lack of trust in Russian managers

08:04.000 --> 08:07.000
who play the leading role of the trademark.

08:07.000 --> 08:10.000
Yes, there are Coca-Cola managers, there are Pepsi-Cola managers,

08:10.000 --> 08:13.000
who have been developing their image for years,

08:13.000 --> 08:16.000
and now they cost billions of dollars.

08:16.000 --> 08:21.000
Of course, not every manager believes that his brand

08:21.000 --> 08:25.000
can be just as famous and profitable.

08:25.000 --> 08:30.000
Although the tendency to think that the cost of non-material assets

08:30.000 --> 08:33.000
is increasing, some companies are starting to do this,

08:33.000 --> 08:35.000
but this is only a small step.

08:35.000 --> 08:39.000
Unfortunately, many managers do not go for this,

08:39.000 --> 08:44.000
considering the costs of image advertising as just a waste of money.

08:44.000 --> 08:47.000
After all, costs for image must be made constantly.

08:47.000 --> 08:51.000
Single-time investments will not help to preserve the image of companies.

08:51.000 --> 08:57.000
Many brands are forgotten only because they stopped spending money on them.

08:57.000 --> 09:02.000
Naturally, not every owner is ready to constantly invest in such resources.

09:02.000 --> 09:06.000
The next reason for the increase in costs for BTL

09:06.000 --> 09:09.000
is the desire to pay for costs in the short term.

09:09.000 --> 09:13.000
BTL shares allow you to get immediate results,

09:13.000 --> 09:16.000
as we have already said, and pay for your costs immediately.

09:16.000 --> 09:19.000
Naturally, costs for image will not be paid immediately,

09:19.000 --> 09:22.000
because this is a long-term strategy of the company.

09:22.000 --> 09:26.000
Not every owner, not every company manager

09:26.000 --> 09:28.000
is ready to invest their money for a long time.

09:28.000 --> 09:33.000
Why? Because today the economy is unstable.

09:33.000 --> 09:36.000
It has become much more stable than it was five years ago,

09:36.000 --> 09:39.000
but, compared to the Western market,

09:39.000 --> 09:48.000
we are still at the stage of waiting for some crisis,

09:48.000 --> 09:50.000
some legislative changes,

09:50.000 --> 09:54.000
which does not allow owners and companies

09:54.000 --> 09:57.000
to hope for a long-term return of their invested money,

09:57.000 --> 09:59.000
their invested financial resources.

09:59.000 --> 10:04.000
The next reason is speculation about the desire of the buyer to receive bonuses.

10:04.000 --> 10:07.000
This is psychology. We all love gifts.

10:07.000 --> 10:11.000
We are pleased to receive them, as it is pleasant to give.

10:11.000 --> 10:15.000
Therefore, any programs to stimulate sales

10:15.000 --> 10:18.000
have such a good result, such a success,

10:18.000 --> 10:23.000
because all customers, including you and me, buy gifts.

10:23.000 --> 10:26.000
The next point is to eliminate the seasonal factor

10:26.000 --> 10:28.000
when selling products.

10:28.000 --> 10:31.000
Any product is seasonal.

10:32.000 --> 10:35.000
Some products are sold for half a year,

10:35.000 --> 10:37.000
and some are not sold for half a year.

10:37.000 --> 10:39.000
Take, for example, mosquito cream.

10:39.000 --> 10:42.000
We can buy it in spring, in summer,

10:42.000 --> 10:46.000
but we do not need it in winter or in autumn.

10:46.000 --> 10:52.000
And any other products are also subject to the influence of seasonality.

10:52.000 --> 10:58.000
The programs to stimulate sales allow us to do a lot.

10:58.000 --> 11:01.000
The first is to increase sales in the low season

11:01.000 --> 11:04.000
in order to stabilize the situation in the company,

11:04.000 --> 11:09.000
and in the high season to take away an additional share of the market from the competitor

11:09.000 --> 11:11.000
or at least keep your share.

11:11.000 --> 11:14.000
The programs to stimulate sales also help.

11:14.000 --> 11:19.000
The next reason is to establish a close relationship with the consumer,

11:19.000 --> 11:22.000
or, as they call it in the West, personalization.

11:22.000 --> 11:25.000
This trend is also going to us from the West,

11:25.000 --> 11:31.000
and there, today, the fashion for personalization has captured all the minds of business.

11:31.000 --> 11:34.000
It is still going to us,

11:34.000 --> 11:37.000
but it is a trend of the future,

11:37.000 --> 11:41.000
when we will have to go out to almost every consumer individually

11:41.000 --> 11:44.000
and meet their requirements.

11:44.000 --> 11:47.000
Naturally, we are allocating segments today

11:47.000 --> 11:52.000
and trying to adjust our proposals to the requirements of a certain group of consumers,

11:53.000 --> 11:59.000
but in the future we will be getting closer and closer to the individual requests of our clients.

11:59.000 --> 12:04.000
Let's look at the place of integrated marketing communications

12:04.000 --> 12:09.000
or promotion tools in the general planning structure.

12:09.000 --> 12:12.000
Here is a slide of the structure of the marketing plan,

12:12.000 --> 12:17.000
a standard document that determines the company's activities for the entire next year.

12:17.000 --> 12:21.000
And despite the fact that this document is called a marketing plan,

12:21.000 --> 12:24.000
it determines the activities of the entire company,

12:24.000 --> 12:27.000
because all the structures involved in it,

12:27.000 --> 12:29.000
who it can be,

12:29.000 --> 12:32.000
this is, of course, the sales department and the marketing department,

12:32.000 --> 12:35.000
this is, of course, the procurement department,

12:35.000 --> 12:39.000
because they buy products at the requirements that the consumer or market presents to us.

12:39.000 --> 12:44.000
This is, of course, the quality department, which monitors the quality of our products.

12:44.000 --> 12:47.000
This is the production department, if we have it,

12:47.000 --> 12:50.000
this is the department that produces our products.

12:50.000 --> 12:53.000
The next department is the personnel department.

12:53.000 --> 12:56.000
Why does it participate in the marketing plan?

12:56.000 --> 13:02.000
Because it provides qualified personnel for achieving the set goals.

13:02.000 --> 13:07.000
And, in fact, this is how we can say about any department that works in the company.

13:07.000 --> 13:10.000
I probably forgot about the finance department,

13:10.000 --> 13:14.000
it is also key in the implementation of the marketing plan,

13:14.000 --> 13:19.000
because it provides financing for the developed document.

13:19.000 --> 13:24.000
Well, the marketing plan is a fairly standard document,

13:24.000 --> 13:27.000
and it is divided into two parts.

13:27.000 --> 13:32.000
The first part is the analysis that marketers do in order to understand where we should go.

13:32.000 --> 13:36.000
And the second part is, of course, the development of the very strategies

13:36.000 --> 13:39.000
on the basis of which the company will operate.

13:39.000 --> 13:41.000
The first of them is the assortment strategy,

13:41.000 --> 13:43.000
when we determine the assortment,

13:43.000 --> 13:47.000
by which we will position and promote ourselves in the market.

13:47.000 --> 13:50.000
The second strategy is the price one,

13:50.000 --> 13:53.000
when we determine at what price, with what discounts or prices,

13:53.000 --> 13:56.000
we will offer our products on the market.

13:56.000 --> 13:59.000
The third strategy is distribution.

13:59.000 --> 14:05.000
Here we consider which channels of sales we will sell our goods and offer it on the market.

14:05.000 --> 14:10.000
And the fourth is just the communication strategy or promotion strategy,

14:10.000 --> 14:13.000
in fact, how we will present ourselves,

14:13.000 --> 14:16.000
how we will talk to our customers about ourselves

14:16.000 --> 14:21.000
and what events we will do in order to implement our plan.

14:21.000 --> 14:24.000
What is included in the communication policy?

14:24.000 --> 14:28.000
Four main tools of promotion are included in the communication policy.

14:28.000 --> 14:32.000
The first is, of course, advertising, and we will talk about it separately.

14:32.000 --> 14:35.000
The second point is the promotion of sales,

14:35.000 --> 14:38.000
these are all events that relate to BTL.

14:38.000 --> 14:42.000
The third point is, of course, PR, and it is highlighted by a separate tool,

14:42.000 --> 14:45.000
because it is really a separate tool of the company,

14:45.000 --> 14:49.000
which allows you to optimize resources and support,

14:49.000 --> 14:52.000
one way or another, to have companies on the market.

14:52.000 --> 14:57.000
And the fourth section, the fourth tool of marketing communications,

14:57.000 --> 15:00.000
is, of course, personal sales.

15:00.000 --> 15:04.000
Personal sales also relate to marketing communications,

15:04.000 --> 15:07.000
because, in fact, in the process of sales,

15:07.000 --> 15:11.000
communication with a specific consumer is carried out.

15:11.000 --> 15:14.000
Let's consider what communication policy is.

15:14.000 --> 15:17.000
Communication policy is the whole set of means

15:17.000 --> 15:23.000
that unites the interaction with all objects of our communications.

15:23.000 --> 15:25.000
The objects are presented on the slide,

15:25.000 --> 15:28.000
and we will talk about each of them separately now.

15:28.000 --> 15:32.000
The first object is, of course, the employees of the company or the personnel of the company.

15:32.000 --> 15:36.000
Very often we forget about this and do not work with our personnel,

15:36.000 --> 15:41.000
but, in fact, the whole communication with our clients begins with them.

15:41.000 --> 15:44.000
And you need to work especially carefully with the personnel.

15:44.000 --> 15:47.000
Try to ask your sales managers a question,

15:47.000 --> 15:50.000
what is best for sale?

15:50.000 --> 15:53.000
Well, there will be one of the following answers.

15:53.000 --> 15:58.000
The first is what I know, the second is what I like personally,

15:58.000 --> 16:00.000
and the third is what is known.

16:00.000 --> 16:05.000
The products are always sold well, and you need to make the least effort.

16:05.000 --> 16:11.000
That is why our task is to convey to the personnel of the company

16:11.000 --> 16:16.000
the attractiveness of the product that we promote and sell.

16:16.000 --> 16:19.000
I will give an example from my experience.

16:19.000 --> 16:23.000
When I worked in one of the companies on the alcohol market,

16:23.000 --> 16:27.000
in addition to the alcohol sector, we also had a tobacco sector.

16:27.000 --> 16:33.000
And in the canteen of the company cigars were sold,

16:33.000 --> 16:37.000
which the company itself offered for sale on the market.

16:37.000 --> 16:40.000
But they did not do very well on the market,

16:40.000 --> 16:43.000
they were not used by the active demand.

16:43.000 --> 16:47.000
And we set ourselves the goal of finding out what was going on,

16:47.000 --> 16:50.000
why they were not so popular,

16:50.000 --> 16:54.000
and tried to start, of course, with the personnel of the company.

16:54.000 --> 16:59.000
We simply organized a tasting of these cigars during a lunch break,

16:59.000 --> 17:02.000
when we invited all the employees of the company,

17:02.000 --> 17:06.000
who naturally smoke, to try to taste these cigars

17:06.000 --> 17:09.000
and fill out the forms that were previously developed.

17:09.000 --> 17:11.000
We killed two birds with one stone.

17:11.000 --> 17:14.000
The first of them was, of course, a survey,

17:14.000 --> 17:17.000
in fact, a market survey,

17:17.000 --> 17:20.000
given that there are quite a lot of employees in the company,

17:20.000 --> 17:22.000
about 2,500 people,

17:22.000 --> 17:26.000
and they represent completely different categories of people,

17:26.000 --> 17:30.000
starting with loaders and ending with top managers of the company.

17:30.000 --> 17:34.000
Naturally, we managed to survey all categories of potential clients.

17:34.000 --> 17:36.000
This is the first point.

17:36.000 --> 17:40.000
And the second point, naturally, was to make such an internal PR,

17:40.000 --> 17:43.000
because people, having tried this product,

17:43.000 --> 17:46.000
first began to buy it from wall companies,

17:46.000 --> 17:50.000
and secondly, to recommend it to their colleagues, friends, acquaintances,

17:50.000 --> 17:54.000
because they themselves knew that it was attractive,

17:54.000 --> 17:57.000
it was interesting, and they liked it.

17:57.000 --> 18:00.000
And such points are very important for the company,

18:00.000 --> 18:03.000
because the more correctly we tell about the product,

18:03.000 --> 18:06.000
the more correctly we position it within the company,

18:06.000 --> 18:08.000
the more it will be sold on the market.

18:08.000 --> 18:11.000
This is the very first step that needs to be taken.

18:11.000 --> 18:14.000
The second point, or the second object of our communications,

18:14.000 --> 18:16.000
is, of course, consumers.

18:16.000 --> 18:18.000
Well, what can I say about this?

18:18.000 --> 18:21.000
The main communications are aimed at our consumers,

18:21.000 --> 18:25.000
because it depends on them whether our company will work successfully on the market,

18:25.000 --> 18:30.000
whether our product will be in demand and loyalty,

18:30.000 --> 18:35.000
whether clients will come again and again for what we offer on the market.

18:35.000 --> 18:38.000
We will talk about this separately.

18:38.000 --> 18:42.000
The next object is marketing intermediaries,

18:42.000 --> 18:47.000
or, to be more precise, our dealers, distributors,

18:47.000 --> 18:49.000
wholesalers, retail networks.

18:49.000 --> 18:51.000
This is a trading channel,

18:51.000 --> 18:56.000
this is the channel that helps to deliver our product to the end consumer.

18:56.000 --> 19:01.000
And here, active events of trade marketing are used.

19:01.000 --> 19:03.000
This is a very important point,

19:03.000 --> 19:08.000
because without this, today, you will simply not be competitive on the market.

19:08.000 --> 19:13.000
We will consider several interesting discount programs,

19:14.000 --> 19:19.000
which can be used for the trade marketing channel.

19:19.000 --> 19:22.000
The next point is our suppliers.

19:22.000 --> 19:26.000
Naturally, suppliers are very important for the company,

19:26.000 --> 19:29.000
because if relations suddenly deteriorate,

19:29.000 --> 19:31.000
or something happens to our suppliers,

19:31.000 --> 19:35.000
we no longer have the products that we have conceived and that we offer on the market.

19:35.000 --> 19:42.000
It is imperative to maintain a very loyal and good relationship with suppliers.

19:42.000 --> 19:47.000
After all, not only the quality of your product depends on this,

19:47.000 --> 19:50.000
but also discounts for you, cost-effectiveness.

19:50.000 --> 19:52.000
The more loyal your relationship with suppliers,

19:52.000 --> 19:57.000
the more likely it is that the cost-effectiveness of your product will be lower and lower.

19:57.000 --> 20:00.000
The next object is competitors.

20:00.000 --> 20:04.000
It is strange to talk about competitors in communication policy,

20:04.000 --> 20:06.000
but nevertheless, let's say.

20:06.000 --> 20:09.000
With competitors, you need to follow the rules of the game.

20:09.000 --> 20:13.000
You need to have a civilized competition.

20:13.000 --> 20:15.000
And we are gradually approaching this,

20:15.000 --> 20:18.000
although not all competitors behave civilizedly on the market.

20:18.000 --> 20:23.000
Nevertheless, my favorite saying is about competitors as about dead.

20:23.000 --> 20:25.000
Either good or nothing.

20:25.000 --> 20:27.000
Here is the compliance with the rules of the game.

20:27.000 --> 20:29.000
Another object is contact audiences,

20:29.000 --> 20:34.000
or those who recommend our product to the market,

20:34.000 --> 20:36.000
but may not sell it themselves.

20:36.000 --> 20:38.000
These may be agents of influence,

20:38.000 --> 20:41.000
these may be people sitting on the streams of information,

