what to focus on,

45:39.000 --> 45:42.000
what to stop,

45:42.000 --> 45:45.000
and how to choose an advertiser.

45:45.000 --> 45:48.000
I want to show you this method

45:48.000 --> 45:51.000
using the example of the elite alcohol market.

45:51.000 --> 45:54.000
We chose advertisers for the end user,

45:54.000 --> 45:57.000
not for the specialists in this market,

45:57.000 --> 46:00.000
but for the end user.

46:00.000 --> 46:03.000
We had three options.

46:03.000 --> 46:06.000
The first one is the industry magazines.

46:06.000 --> 46:09.000
There are many industry magazines,

46:09.000 --> 46:12.000
such as the Wine Club,

46:12.000 --> 46:15.000
which can be read by the customers

46:15.000 --> 46:18.000
in the specialized shops.

46:18.000 --> 46:21.000
There is also a TV channel

46:21.000 --> 46:24.000
where we can advertise our product.

46:24.000 --> 46:27.000
However, there is a special feature.

46:27.000 --> 46:30.000
According to the law,

46:30.000 --> 46:33.000
you cannot advertise alcohol products

46:33.000 --> 46:36.000
on TV screens.

46:36.000 --> 46:39.000
If we decide to do this,

46:39.000 --> 46:42.000
we will have to look for some other options.

46:42.000 --> 46:45.000
The third option is the media,

46:45.000 --> 46:48.000
such as newspapers.

46:48.000 --> 46:51.000
It is not interesting to advertise alcohol products

46:51.000 --> 46:54.000
in the newspapers,

46:54.000 --> 46:57.000
but there you need your own approach.

46:57.000 --> 47:00.000
You need to find interesting stories,

47:00.000 --> 47:03.000
historical events, facts

47:03.000 --> 47:06.000
and the way of life of the consumer.

47:06.000 --> 47:09.000
We chose these three options

47:09.000 --> 47:12.000
and we had to decide

47:12.000 --> 47:15.000
where we will present ourselves,

47:15.000 --> 47:18.000
where it is more profitable,

47:18.000 --> 47:21.000
where it is more interesting and where it is better.

47:21.000 --> 47:24.000
We chose the following criteria for the assessment.

47:24.000 --> 47:27.000
The first criterion is the volume of the publication.

47:27.000 --> 47:30.000
How many customers can apply to this media?

47:31.000 --> 47:34.000
If you look at the table,

47:34.000 --> 47:37.000
you will see that the largest audience

47:37.000 --> 47:40.000
is television, newspapers and the press.

47:43.000 --> 47:46.000
The next criterion is the volume of the appeal.

47:46.000 --> 47:49.000
This is the volume that shows

47:49.000 --> 47:52.000
how many of the end consumers

47:52.000 --> 47:55.000
will watch this newspaper.

47:55.000 --> 47:58.000
Here you can see that newspapers and newspapers

47:59.000 --> 48:02.000
account for a little more than television.

48:02.000 --> 48:05.000
The next criterion is the audience of the carrier.

48:05.000 --> 48:08.000
Here we look at the main audience.

48:08.000 --> 48:11.000
We see that in specialized magazines

48:11.000 --> 48:14.000
the main audience is the elite alcohol market specialists.

48:14.000 --> 48:17.000
If we take television or newspapers,

48:17.000 --> 48:20.000
there are, of course, end consumers.

48:20.000 --> 48:23.000
Our goal in this assessment is, of course,

48:23.000 --> 48:26.000
end consumers.

48:26.000 --> 48:29.000
The next criterion is the probability of getting acquainted.

48:29.000 --> 48:32.000
That is, the probability that people will get to your information,

48:32.000 --> 48:35.000
read it, see it, hear it, and so on.

48:35.000 --> 48:38.000
The greatest probability of getting acquainted

48:38.000 --> 48:41.000
is, of course, industry magazines,

48:41.000 --> 48:44.000
because people take them on purpose

48:44.000 --> 48:47.000
to read, watch, and so on.

48:47.000 --> 48:50.000
The next criterion is the probability of getting acquainted

48:50.000 --> 48:53.000
is, of course, television,

48:53.000 --> 48:56.000
because if people watch this program,

48:56.000 --> 48:59.000
they will see our advertising, our product.

48:59.000 --> 49:02.000
The least likely to get acquainted is, of course, newspapers.

49:02.000 --> 49:05.000
Newspapers are large, there are many strips,

49:05.000 --> 49:08.000
and the probability is very small

49:08.000 --> 49:11.000
that our customer will read one or another note

49:11.000 --> 49:14.000
or see one or another ad or one or another interesting story.

49:14.000 --> 49:17.000
The next criterion is the rate of accumulation.

49:17.000 --> 49:20.000
Here we assessed

49:20.000 --> 49:23.000
how often a certain program, newspaper, or magazine was published.

49:23.000 --> 49:26.000
That is, how often this information

49:26.000 --> 49:29.000
will be accumulated by our customers.

49:29.000 --> 49:32.000
And here the rate of accumulation

49:32.000 --> 49:35.000
is the lowest, of course, for an industry magazine,

49:35.000 --> 49:38.000
because it is published only once a month.

49:38.000 --> 49:41.000
The next criterion is the cost of advertising space.

49:41.000 --> 49:44.000
Well, of course, the cost is the most expensive for television.

49:44.000 --> 49:47.000
The second place is for industry magazines,

49:47.000 --> 49:50.000
the cost of space is quite high,

49:50.000 --> 49:53.000
and the third place is for newspapers.

49:53.000 --> 49:56.000
And the last criterion is the useful audience and the degree of penetration.

49:56.000 --> 49:59.000
What is this criterion?

49:59.000 --> 50:02.000
This criterion shows how many of our clients' audience

50:02.000 --> 50:05.000
we target advertising.

50:05.000 --> 50:08.000
And here you see that the largest percentage

50:08.000 --> 50:11.000
is, of course, television.

50:11.000 --> 50:14.000
And the smallest is industry magazines,

50:14.000 --> 50:17.000
because among those who will read these magazines

50:17.000 --> 50:20.000
there are very few end consumers.

50:20.000 --> 50:23.000
When we assessed all the criteria,

50:23.000 --> 50:26.000
we carried out the so-called scaling.

50:26.000 --> 50:29.000
That is, we determined the scale according to each criterion

50:29.000 --> 50:32.000
in order to score.

50:32.000 --> 50:35.000
We scored, added these points,

50:35.000 --> 50:38.000
and as a result we got a total score,

50:38.000 --> 50:41.000
according to which we actually determined

50:41.000 --> 50:44.000
the most attractive media carrier.

50:44.000 --> 50:47.000
In the example presented,

50:47.000 --> 50:50.000
the largest point was received by television.

50:50.000 --> 50:53.000
And, in fact, we did.

50:53.000 --> 50:56.000
We advertised our product in the program «Столько одному».

50:56.000 --> 50:59.000
And even the fact that it was not allowed to advertise alcohol

50:59.000 --> 51:02.000
