52:00.000 --> 52:03.000
the result you planned.

52:03.000 --> 52:06.000
Let's consider the main reasons

52:06.000 --> 52:09.000
for the low effectiveness of advertising.

52:09.000 --> 52:12.000
There are several of them.

52:12.000 --> 52:15.000
The first one is, of course, the incorrect setting of the goal

52:15.000 --> 52:18.000
and task of the advertising campaign.

52:18.000 --> 52:21.000
What does it mean?

52:21.000 --> 52:24.000
It means that your goals are set without numbers.

52:24.000 --> 52:27.000
They are not clearly and concretely set.

52:27.000 --> 52:30.000
And, of course, you cannot assess whether your campaign

52:30.000 --> 52:33.000
has increased the market share.

52:33.000 --> 52:36.000
According to the results of the advertising campaign,

52:36.000 --> 52:39.000
you increased your market share by about 1%.

52:39.000 --> 52:42.000
Is it good or bad?

52:42.000 --> 52:45.000
Nobody knows whether it is good or bad.

52:45.000 --> 52:48.000
Maybe the competitor increased its share by 5% at that time.

52:48.000 --> 52:51.000
Then you were late.

52:51.000 --> 52:54.000
That is why in order to clearly understand whether your campaign

52:54.000 --> 52:57.000
has worked or not, you need to set goals very competently,

52:57.000 --> 53:00.000
then you can assess whether you have worked effectively or not.

53:00.000 --> 53:03.000
The next mistake we make

53:03.000 --> 53:06.000
is that we do not have the information of the buyers.

53:06.000 --> 53:09.000
We do not know where they get the information.

53:09.000 --> 53:12.000
I will give an example.

53:12.000 --> 53:15.000
I worked on a consulting project

53:15.000 --> 53:18.000
with the director of a company

53:18.000 --> 53:21.000
that produced equipment for the food industry.

53:21.000 --> 53:24.000
The main problem was that the company's

53:24.000 --> 53:27.000
production was not well-known to the public.

53:27.000 --> 53:30.000
The main problem was to advertise our products.

53:30.000 --> 53:33.000
So, advertising was done everywhere,

53:33.000 --> 53:36.000
in principle, competently,

53:36.000 --> 53:39.000
in industry sources,

53:39.000 --> 53:42.000
in mass media,

53:42.000 --> 53:45.000
at exhibitions, conferences, everything as it should be.

53:45.000 --> 53:48.000
But there was no result.

53:48.000 --> 53:51.000
The clients did not come.

53:51.000 --> 53:54.000
We found out that they get the information

53:54.000 --> 53:57.000
from their colleagues in the workshop,

53:57.000 --> 54:00.000
consult, ask for recommendations.

54:00.000 --> 54:03.000
And this is the main source of information

54:03.000 --> 54:06.000
about a particular product in this case.

54:06.000 --> 54:09.000
Therefore, ask.

54:09.000 --> 54:12.000
This way you can optimize your resources

54:12.000 --> 54:15.000
and not advertise everywhere.

54:15.000 --> 54:18.000
The next mistake is the lack of feedback from the consumer.

54:18.000 --> 54:21.000
You can evaluate the effectiveness

54:21.000 --> 54:24.000
if you do not know where they come from,

54:24.000 --> 54:27.000
whether they learned about you from this source.

54:27.000 --> 54:30.000
Companies that specialize in this person

54:30.000 --> 54:33.000
do it very well.

54:33.000 --> 54:36.000
And they ask,

54:36.000 --> 54:39.000
where did you learn about our company,

54:39.000 --> 54:42.000
from which source?

54:42.000 --> 54:45.000
Only then you can evaluate

54:45.000 --> 54:48.000
and you will never be able to understand

54:48.000 --> 54:51.000
whether you spent your money effectively or not.

54:51.000 --> 54:54.000
The next main mistake is segmentation.

54:54.000 --> 54:57.000
Very often we just forget about it.

54:57.000 --> 55:00.000
It seems to us that we know the circle of our clients,

55:00.000 --> 55:03.000
we know who they are, what they do, what they do.

55:03.000 --> 55:06.000
But in fact, segmentation gives very high costs.

55:06.000 --> 55:09.000
We shoot at the sparrows with guns

55:09.000 --> 55:12.000
because we want to advertise for everyone.

55:13.000 --> 55:16.000
We ask our customers.

55:16.000 --> 55:19.000
All ages from 15 to 60 years old.

55:19.000 --> 55:22.000
This is not segmentation.

55:22.000 --> 55:25.000
Segmentation is the allocation of a clear group of consumers

55:25.000 --> 55:28.000
who make certain requirements for your product.

55:28.000 --> 55:31.000
Based on these requirements,

55:31.000 --> 55:34.000
you can make an advertising campaign,

55:34.000 --> 55:37.000
and not just general words, general videos, general advertising,

55:37.000 --> 55:40.000
which will not give a result,

55:41.000 --> 55:44.000
but will be just general information for your customers.

55:44.000 --> 55:47.000
The next main point, which can be divided into two.

55:47.000 --> 55:50.000
