56:09.000 --> 56:12.000
But they have never faced this.

56:12.000 --> 56:15.000
They learn for our money and spend no less

56:15.000 --> 56:18.000
than if you paid a qualified specialist.

56:18.000 --> 56:21.000
And the second point.

56:21.000 --> 56:24.000
You can contact an advertising agency

56:24.000 --> 56:27.000
and they will do this job for you.

56:27.000 --> 56:30.000
Then your company just needs an organizer,

56:30.000 --> 56:33.000
coordinator of activities.

56:33.000 --> 56:36.000
This is easier and more important.

56:37.000 --> 56:40.000
You can contact an agency,

56:40.000 --> 56:43.000
which will work either professionally or not.

56:43.000 --> 56:46.000
Here is the recommendation.

56:46.000 --> 56:49.000
Choose the agency you work with carefully.

56:49.000 --> 56:52.000
Try to work with an agency that has already had experience

56:52.000 --> 56:55.000
in your market.

56:55.000 --> 56:58.000
With the same goal,

56:58.000 --> 57:01.000
so that they do not learn for your money.

57:01.000 --> 57:04.000
The next mistake is the lack of consistency

57:04.000 --> 57:07.000
and the lack of communication.

57:07.000 --> 57:10.000
What does this mean?

57:10.000 --> 57:13.000
It means that we act according to the policy of digging a hole.

57:13.000 --> 57:16.000
We have a problem, we need to solve it.

57:16.000 --> 57:19.000
We run to marketers and say,

57:19.000 --> 57:22.000
guys, let's urgently do something with this.

57:22.000 --> 57:25.000
And so we eliminate the consequences of certain actions.

57:25.000 --> 57:28.000
We do not prevent our failures,

57:28.000 --> 57:31.000
but we solve them.

57:31.000 --> 57:34.000
We try to minimize all these things.

57:34.000 --> 57:37.000
Therefore, an advertising campaign should be developed,

57:37.000 --> 57:40.000
which takes place regularly,

57:40.000 --> 57:43.000
which warns of the development of certain situations,

57:43.000 --> 57:46.000
which are unfavorably reflected in our business.

57:46.000 --> 57:49.000
In the light of mistakes,

57:49.000 --> 57:52.000
let's look at examples of so-called stupid advertising.

57:52.000 --> 57:55.000
These are the examples of the most common mistakes.

57:55.000 --> 57:58.000
The first mistake is that the company does not have a plan.

57:58.000 --> 58:01.000
These posters, these banners,

58:01.000 --> 58:04.000
are posted on the Internet.

58:04.000 --> 58:07.000
Here are two examples.

58:07.000 --> 58:10.000
The first is an upside-down banner with its head down.

58:10.000 --> 58:13.000
You know, there was an idea,

58:13.000 --> 58:16.000
maybe they did it on purpose

58:16.000 --> 58:19.000
to attract attention,

58:19.000 --> 58:22.000
but then at least they wrote the phone number.

58:22.000 --> 58:25.000
And so, imagine, who will see this ad?

58:25.000 --> 58:28.000
And they will never read it.

58:28.000 --> 58:31.000
The money is thrown into the wind.

58:31.000 --> 58:34.000
Another ad.

58:34.000 --> 58:37.000
Our company Euroseed is famous for its hypocrisy.

58:37.000 --> 58:40.000
I don't know how to evaluate it,

58:40.000 --> 58:43.000
whether this is stupid advertising or not.

58:43.000 --> 58:46.000
Of course, it is remembered.

58:46.000 --> 58:49.000
Maybe it was the purpose of the advertising campaign.

58:49.000 --> 58:52.000
Then it's probably good.

58:52.000 --> 58:55.000
How does it combine?

58:55.000 --> 58:58.000
It's not clear.

58:58.000 --> 59:01.000
Three more examples from the same series.

59:01.000 --> 59:04.000
The first is beer advertising.

59:04.000 --> 59:07.000
The taste of the frozen sun tells us

59:07.000 --> 59:10.000
a slogan that is written there.

59:10.000 --> 59:13.000
You can't come up with a more ridiculous slogan for beer.

59:13.000 --> 59:16.000
The frozen sun gives away the coldness,

59:16.000 --> 59:19.000
gives away something unpleasant,

59:19.000 --> 59:22.000
negative.

59:22.000 --> 59:25.000
Of course, it is unlikely to be in favor of this beer,

59:25.000 --> 59:28.000
this product.

59:28.000 --> 59:31.000
Another ad,

59:31.000 --> 59:34.000
you know, in the style of the 40s-50s,

59:34.000 --> 59:37.000
when the war was going on,

59:37.000 --> 59:40.000
and there was advertising,

59:40.000 --> 59:43.000
you signed up as a volunteer.

59:43.000 --> 59:46.000
Here is something like that.

59:46.000 --> 59:49.000
This is not a combined ad with a brand.

59:49.000 --> 59:52.000
It is very interesting how the buyers of this brand

59:52.000 --> 59:55.000
reacted to such advertising.

59:55.000 --> 59:58.000
Another ad, car wash.

59:58.000 --> 01:00:01.000
Men like it most of all.

01:00:01.000 --> 01:00:04.000
They say that if they saw such advertising,

01:00:04.000 --> 01:00:07.000
they would definitely stop by this car wash.

01:00:07.000 --> 01:00:10.000
Nevertheless, you see what is written there.

01:00:10.000 --> 01:00:13.000
No comments.

01:00:16.000 --> 01:00:19.000
PR

01:00:24.000 --> 01:00:27.000
Now let's move on to the consideration of PR functions.

01:00:27.000 --> 01:00:30.000
PR or public communication

01:00:30.000 --> 01:00:33.000
is what allows companies to maintain

01:00:33.000 --> 01:00:36.000
their target audience,

01:00:36.000 --> 01:00:39.000
to constantly communicate with customers.

01:00:39.000 --> 01:00:42.000
Moreover, more often

01:00:42.000 --> 01:00:45.000
these are free means of communication

01:00:45.000 --> 01:00:48.000
with the media.

01:00:48.000 --> 01:00:51.000
Attracting media,

01:00:51.000 --> 01:00:54.000
journalists, various publications,

01:00:54.000 --> 01:00:57.000
newspapers,

01:00:57.000 --> 01:01:00.000
to cover the events in your company for free.

01:01:00.000 --> 01:01:03.000
What are the main functions that PR has?

01:01:03.000 --> 01:01:06.000
The first is, of course,

01:01:06.000 --> 01:01:09.000
establishing trust between the company itself

01:01:09.000 --> 01:01:12.000
and the public,

01:01:12.000 --> 01:01:15.000
as well as as consumers

01:01:15.000 --> 01:01:18.000
and as a media outlet.

01:01:24.000 --> 01:01:27.000
The second is to create a positive image of the company.

01:01:27.000 --> 01:01:30.000
After all, nothing works like that

01:01:30.000 --> 01:01:33.000
on the image of the company,

01:01:33.000 --> 01:01:36.000
as a positive image of the company

01:01:36.000 --> 01:01:39.000
that performs a charity activity,

01:01:39.000 --> 01:01:42.000
holds sponsorship projects,

01:01:42.000 --> 01:01:45.000
constantly announces itself,

01:01:45.000 --> 01:01:48.000
reminds about itself.

01:01:48.000 --> 01:01:51.000
It seems, why do this?

01:01:51.000 --> 01:01:54.000
Nevertheless, even Gazprom,

01:01:54.000 --> 01:01:57.000
which seems to be not needed for advertising,

01:01:57.000 --> 01:02:00.000
performs a constant PR activity,

01:02:00.000 --> 01:02:03.000
constantly reminds about itself.

01:02:03.000 --> 01:02:06.000
The Russian Railway Company,

01:02:06.000 --> 01:02:09.000
for example,

01:02:09.000 --> 01:02:12.000
performs a special activity

01:02:12.000 --> 01:02:15.000
in the form of loyalty to the client,

01:02:15.000 --> 01:02:18.000
in the form of a reminder,

01:02:18.000 --> 01:02:21.000
in the form of a strong, stable, powerful image of the company.

01:02:21.000 --> 01:02:24.000
The next point is to preserve the reputation of the company.

01:02:24.000 --> 01:02:27.000
When is this function applied?

01:02:27.000 --> 01:02:30.000
When there is a crisis in the company

01:02:30.000 --> 01:02:33.000
or some negative things happen.

01:02:33.000 --> 01:02:36.000
It is important to preserve the reputation of the company,

01:02:36.000 --> 01:02:39.000
to come out with a proud face from any situation,

01:02:39.000 --> 01:02:42.000
to interact with the media

01:02:42.000 --> 01:02:45.000
and with the company itself

01:02:45.000 --> 01:02:48.000
so that some negative information

01:02:48.000 --> 01:02:51.000
does not seep into the market

01:02:51.000 --> 01:02:54.000
for the clients and consumers.

01:02:54.000 --> 01:02:57.000
The next main function is internal PR.

01:02:57.000 --> 01:03:00.000
The employees feel that they work

01:03:01.000 --> 01:03:04.000
in a strong and stable company.

01:03:04.000 --> 01:03:07.000
This works to preserve the personnel reserve,

01:03:07.000 --> 01:03:10.000
to preserve the personnel potential,

01:03:10.000 --> 01:03:13.000
to attract new employees, more qualified,

01:03:13.000 --> 01:03:16.000
if the company positions itself as strong,

01:03:16.000 --> 01:03:19.000
if it constantly announces about itself.

01:03:19.000 --> 01:03:22.000
Moreover, it works very well

01:03:22.000 --> 01:03:25.000
for sales in this sense.

01:03:25.000 --> 01:03:28.000
If the employees are loyal to the company,

01:03:28.000 --> 01:03:31.000
they work better and achieve better results.

01:03:31.000 --> 01:03:34.000
Another point is to expand the sphere of the company's influence.

01:03:34.000 --> 01:03:37.000
It is especially important

01:03:37.000 --> 01:03:40.000
when the owner of the company

01:03:40.000 --> 01:03:43.000
or the manager plans

01:03:43.000 --> 01:03:46.000
to carry out political or social activities.

01:03:46.000 --> 01:03:49.000
Naturally, PR is more important here

01:03:49.000 --> 01:03:52.000
because it influences the relationship

01:03:52.000 --> 01:03:55.000
with the authorities,

01:03:55.000 --> 01:03:58.000
with the public.

01:03:58.000 --> 01:04:01.000
We have already said that PR is expensive

01:04:01.000 --> 01:04:04.000
and it should be done constantly and regularly

01:04:04.000 --> 01:04:07.000
because single programs

01:04:07.000 --> 01:04:10.000
will not give you a targeted result.

01:04:10.000 --> 01:04:13.000
Remember the example of expensive costumes.

01:04:13.000 --> 01:04:16.000
If you bought an expensive costume,

01:04:16.000 --> 01:04:19.000
it does not give you anything.

01:04:19.000 --> 01:04:22.000
You need to go further,

01:04:23.000 --> 01:04:26.000
to announce about yourself,

01:04:26.000 --> 01:04:29.000
to support your business.

01:04:29.000 --> 01:04:32.000
The company should continue this activity

01:04:32.000 --> 01:04:35.000
by constantly supporting the opinion

01:04:35.000 --> 01:04:38.000
of its customers at the same level,

01:04:38.000 --> 01:04:41.000
without falling below.

01:04:41.000 --> 01:04:44.000
What are the main stages of the development

01:04:44.000 --> 01:04:47.000
of PR events?

01:04:47.000 --> 01:04:50.000
There are several of them,

01:04:51.000 --> 01:04:54.000
but we analyze them first.

01:04:54.000 --> 01:04:57.000
We look at where and how we can hold

01:04:57.000 --> 01:05:00.000
this campaign.

01:05:00.000 --> 01:05:03.000
Naturally, this is followed by a task.

01:05:03.000 --> 01:05:06.000
We must clearly understand

01:05:06.000 --> 01:05:09.000
what we want to achieve with this event,

01:05:09.000 --> 01:05:12.000
what we do it for,

01:05:12.000 --> 01:05:15.000
what opinion we want to leave in the eyes of customers.

01:05:15.000 --> 01:05:18.000
When the task is determined,

01:05:18.000 --> 01:05:21.000
we choose the agency and develop a program.

01:05:21.000 --> 01:05:24.000
It is great when this program is developed

01:05:24.000 --> 01:05:27.000
for a long time, for example, for a year,

01:05:27.000 --> 01:05:30.000
and not a one-time campaign.

01:05:30.000 --> 01:05:33.000
In any case,

01:05:33.000 --> 01:05:36.000
if you do it once or make a plan for a year,

01:05:36.000 --> 01:05:39.000
the agency will need your help.

01:05:39.000 --> 01:05:42.000
When you have made a plan,

01:05:42.000 --> 01:05:45.000
the next step is to develop a cost.

01:05:45.000 --> 01:05:48.000
We calculate how much we need

01:05:48.000 --> 01:05:51.000
to implement this program.

01:05:51.000 --> 01:05:54.000
The next step is to implement the program itself.

01:05:54.000 --> 01:05:57.000
What I would like to say here is that

01:05:57.000 --> 01:06:00.000
usually PR events are very clearly scheduled

01:06:00.000 --> 01:06:03.000
and timed,

01:06:03.000 --> 01:06:06.000
because they are strictly limited in time.

01:06:06.000 --> 01:06:09.000
Of course, this timing must be adhered to.

01:06:09.000 --> 01:06:12.000
In the same way,

01:06:13.000 --> 01:06:16.000
this work together with the agency and the company

01:06:16.000 --> 01:06:19.000
needs to be controlled.

01:06:19.000 --> 01:06:22.000
The last and final step is to assess the event,

01:06:22.000 --> 01:06:25.000
how it went,

01:06:25.000 --> 01:06:28.000
what went well, what went wrong,

01:06:28.000 --> 01:06:31.000
where we made mistakes, what we did not take into account.

01:06:31.000 --> 01:06:34.000
This is an important point,

01:06:34.000 --> 01:06:37.000
because any event you have held

01:06:37.000 --> 01:06:40.000
is not only about PR,

01:06:41.000 --> 01:06:44.000
but also about any other event you hold in the company.

01:06:44.000 --> 01:06:47.000
These are advertising campaigns,

01:06:47.000 --> 01:06:50.000
promotion campaigns, PR campaigns.

01:06:50.000 --> 01:06:53.000
Put everything into the database,

01:06:53.000 --> 01:06:56.000
create your own database,

01:06:56.000 --> 01:06:59.000
because only by the results of certain events

01:06:59.000 --> 01:07:02.000
you can predict the future effectiveness

01:07:02.000 --> 01:07:05.000
and decide whether to repeat this event or not,

01:07:05.000 --> 01:07:08.000
continue this activity or not.

01:07:09.000 --> 01:07:12.000
You can only help the company you attract.

01:07:12.000 --> 01:07:15.000
If they have held certain events,

01:07:15.000 --> 01:07:18.000
they will be able to help you

01:07:18.000 --> 01:07:21.000
and predict the future effectiveness

01:07:21.000 --> 01:07:24.000
and the result,

01:07:24.000 --> 01:07:27.000
whether you will get what you expect or not.

01:07:27.000 --> 01:07:30.000
I would like to emphasize one more thing.

01:07:30.000 --> 01:07:33.000
When assessing the event,

01:07:33.000 --> 01:07:36.000
you must be sure that

01:07:37.000 --> 01:07:40.000
any event related to public communication

01:07:40.000 --> 01:07:43.000
does not give you a increase in sales for the day after tomorrow.

01:07:43.000 --> 01:07:46.000
I have already repeated this,

01:07:46.000 --> 01:07:49.000
but I had an experience

01:07:49.000 --> 01:07:52.000
when we held a sponsorship event.

01:07:52.000 --> 01:07:55.000
Our company was a sponsor of the Kremlin Cup of Ballroom Dancing.

01:07:55.000 --> 01:07:58.000
The event was wonderful,

01:07:58.000 --> 01:08:01.000
we had a lot of participants,

01:08:01.000 --> 01:08:04.000
and we were able to make a lot of money.

01:08:05.000 --> 01:08:08.000
We worked with the organizers of the event,

01:08:08.000 --> 01:08:11.000
we were always present,

01:08:11.000 --> 01:08:14.000
we held promotions,

01:08:14.000 --> 01:08:17.000
we awarded winners.

01:08:17.000 --> 01:08:20.000
Everything was great.

01:08:20.000 --> 01:08:23.000
The only thing that upset me a little

01:08:23.000 --> 01:08:26.000
after this event

01:08:26.000 --> 01:08:29.000
was that the owner invited me to his house

01:08:29.000 --> 01:08:32.000
and asked me where the increase in sales was.

01:08:33.000 --> 01:08:36.000
I told him to warn his managers

01:08:36.000 --> 01:08:39.000
that the increase in sales would not happen for the day after tomorrow.

01:08:39.000 --> 01:08:42.000
This is a work on an image

01:08:42.000 --> 01:08:45.000
that is built on a long-term basis.

01:08:45.000 --> 01:08:48.000
What are the main methods of PR?

01:08:48.000 --> 01:08:51.000
What actually helps us to work on this?

01:08:51.000 --> 01:08:54.000
What events?

01:08:54.000 --> 01:08:57.000
The first is the relationship with various journalists,

01:08:57.000 --> 01:09:00.000
with the media, mass media, etc.

01:09:01.000 --> 01:09:04.000
We can release various press releases,

01:09:04.000 --> 01:09:07.000
and there is a new product,

01:09:07.000 --> 01:09:10.000
and the press releases are usually free.

01:09:10.000 --> 01:09:13.000
The main thing is to make an interesting press release

01:09:13.000 --> 01:09:16.000
so that the media, newspapers, magazines,

01:09:16.000 --> 01:09:19.000
and TV channels can tell about it.

01:09:19.000 --> 01:09:22.000
This is interesting for your clients and consumers.

01:09:26.000 --> 01:09:29.000
The next thing is the interaction with the media.

01:09:29.000 --> 01:09:32.000
This is an interview with your management,

01:09:32.000 --> 01:09:35.000
your owners, managers, top managers,

01:09:35.000 --> 01:09:38.000
who give interviews about the company's activities,

01:09:38.000 --> 01:09:41.000
its plans,

01:09:41.000 --> 01:09:44.000
the results of the activities,

01:09:44.000 --> 01:09:47.000
which are published in various magazines,

01:09:47.000 --> 01:09:50.000
in industry magazines,

01:09:50.000 --> 01:09:53.000
in the general economic,

01:09:53.000 --> 01:09:56.000
in any media that your clients read.

01:09:56.000 --> 01:09:59.000
This is a very important moment,

01:09:59.000 --> 01:10:02.000
because they will remember you,

01:10:02.000 --> 01:10:05.000
they will know about you,

01:10:05.000 --> 01:10:08.000
they will talk about you.

01:10:08.000 --> 01:10:11.000
The next method of PR is various printed products.

01:10:11.000 --> 01:10:14.000
These are our catalogs, booklets,

01:10:14.000 --> 01:10:17.000
press releases,

01:10:17.000 --> 01:10:20.000
which we distribute at exhibitions,

01:10:20.000 --> 01:10:23.000
seminars, conferences,

01:10:23.000 --> 01:10:26.000
where we talk about our experience,

01:10:26.000 --> 01:10:29.000
what we have achieved,

01:10:29.000 --> 01:10:32.000
what results we have obtained,

01:10:32.000 --> 01:10:35.000
what plans we have.

01:10:35.000 --> 01:10:38.000
This is what we want,

01:10:38.000 --> 01:10:41.000
this is what positions us in the eyes of our clients.

01:10:41.000 --> 01:10:44.000
Corporate publications can also serve as a PR method.

01:10:44.000 --> 01:10:47.000
The next one of the main methods is photo and film production.

01:10:47.000 --> 01:10:50.000
What is it about?

01:10:50.000 --> 01:10:53.000
It is very popular today,

01:10:53.000 --> 01:10:56.000
because we build our trademark,

01:10:56.000 --> 01:10:59.000
our product into certain film and photo plots.

01:10:59.000 --> 01:11:02.000
Why?

01:11:02.000 --> 01:11:05.000
In order to constantly remind our customers

01:11:05.000 --> 01:11:08.000
that this is our product, this is our brand,

01:11:08.000 --> 01:11:11.000
and how we position ourselves.

01:11:11.000 --> 01:11:14.000
This is a very effective method,

01:11:14.000 --> 01:11:17.000
and the costs for product placement are growing year by year.

01:11:17.000 --> 01:11:20.000
If you buy a certain film or article

01:11:20.000 --> 01:11:23.000
and you see that certain trademark is being repeated,

01:11:23.000 --> 01:11:26.000
or you hear about them,

01:11:26.000 --> 01:11:29.000
then it is definitely product placement.

01:11:29.000 --> 01:11:32.000
The advantage of this method is that it is repeated.

01:11:32.000 --> 01:11:35.000
You pay once,

01:11:35.000 --> 01:11:38.000
and the film or series is released several times,

01:11:38.000 --> 01:11:41.000
and customers constantly see it and remember your brand.

01:11:41.000 --> 01:11:44.000
Of course,

01:11:44.000 --> 01:11:47.000
you can buy it again and again,

01:11:47.000 --> 01:11:50.000
gaining loyalty.

01:11:50.000 --> 01:11:53.000
The next one of the main methods is oral speech.

01:11:53.000 --> 01:11:56.000
This is the presentation of companies

01:11:56.000 --> 01:11:59.000
at any public event.

01:11:59.000 --> 01:12:02.000
Conferences, exhibitions,

01:12:02.000 --> 01:12:05.000
press conferences,

01:12:05.000 --> 01:12:08.000
some scientific reports.

01:12:08.000 --> 01:12:11.000
Any speech by your company

01:12:11.000 --> 01:12:14.000
is a PR method.

01:12:14.000 --> 01:12:17.000
Therefore, the company must clearly monitor

01:12:17.000 --> 01:12:20.000
where its employees are speaking,

01:12:20.000 --> 01:12:23.000
what they are saying,

01:12:23.000 --> 01:12:26.000
because they are currently the face of the company

01:12:26.000 --> 01:12:29.000
and a representative of its target audience.

01:12:29.000 --> 01:12:32.000
Another method is sponsorship.

01:12:32.000 --> 01:12:35.000
Participation in various associations,

01:12:35.000 --> 01:12:38.000
trade chambers,

01:12:38.000 --> 01:12:41.000
or associations that care about social issues.

01:12:41.000 --> 01:12:44.000
It is great if you participate in social projects

01:12:44.000 --> 01:12:47.000
and talk about it.

